AWS Application Migration Service (MGN) is a highly automated lift-and-shift (rehost) solution that simplifies, expedites, and reduces the cost of migrating applications to AWS. It allows companies to lift-and-shift a large number of physical, virtual, or cloud servers without compatibility issues, performance disruption, or long cutover windows. Application Migration Service replicates source servers into your AWS account. When you‚Äôre ready, it automatically converts and launches your servers on AWS so you can quickly benefit from the cost savings, productivity, resilience, and agility of the cloud. Once your applications are running on AWS, you can leverage AWS services and capabilities to quickly and easily replatform or refactor those applications ‚Äì which makes lift-and-shift a fast route to modernization.

AWS Application Migration Service - Accelerates and simplifies migration by converting source servers to run natively on AWS.
AWS native services = Fully managed cloud services provided by AWS that require no manual installation, infrastructure management, or patching.

Steps:
Identify the Physical, Virtual and Cloud Servers that needs to be migrated to AWS.
Install Agents - Install AWS Replication Agent on your source servers
Create Replication Template.. usually public subnet
Replicate to AWS - Continue normal business operations while servers are replicated
Perform tests - Perform non-dsruptive tests
Execute Cutover - Your server are launched on AWS within minutes..

Advantages: Highly automated solution, Cutover windows of minutes and no data loss, Large scale migrations with no performance impact, Reduce the cost of migrating and modernizing applications..

Wave 1 -  we do migrations wave by wave..

MGN replication subnet - public subnet , MGN replication instance that takes care of replication..

it can be non aws servers, physical on prem, hypervisors.. 

TCP - 443 for authentication, TCP - 1500 for replication.. data all encrypted during migration.

Creation of Replication Instance and Conversion Instance taken care by AWS MGN service.

Least Privileage model..

