üìå Difference between Wave vs Application in AWS MGN
üìå How to design waves for a real enterprise migration
üìå Best practices for building wave groups

Just tell me!


Yes üëá

You can migrate without a connector IF you:

Install MGN agent manually

Know all server details

Manage server list manually

Configure launch templates manually

This is fine for small migrations (5‚Äì20 servers).

But‚Ä¶

‚ùå Not practical for 500+ servers
‚ùå No auto-discovery
‚ùå No metadata population
‚ùå A lot of manual work
‚ùå Higher chances of error


We use MGN Connectors for large-scale migrations because they automatically discover on-prem servers, integrate with vCenter, bulk-register machines into AWS MGN, and provide accurate metadata needed for replication and launch template creation.

Without the connector, all this work must be done manually, which does not scale for hundreds or thousands of servers.